"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809609","Department of Health","false","2017-12-22","<p>The product information refers to irreversible neuropathic conditions, which are conditions affecting the nervous system.</p><p>The product information states that neuropsychiatric adverse reactions, such as mood disturbances, psychosis and vestibular disorders, may occur during treatment and includes warnings and precautions to minimise these risks. Some of these reactions may persist, but it has not been established whether these are permanent.</p><p>Mefloquine is effective in the prevention and treatment of malaria and is approved by the Medicines and Health products Regulatory Agency (MHRA), which regulates medication in the United Kingdom. As with all medicines, the MHRA keeps the safety of mefloquine under continual review. Mefloquine continues to be recommended as a safe and effective form of malaria prevention by the Advisory Committee on Malaria Prevention, the World Health Organization and other respected organisations who take account of the body of global evidence.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-12-22T12:43:50.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809609/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809609/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809609/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-19","Mefloquine","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord O'Shaughnessy on 19 December (HL3942), whether they consider (1) suicide, and (2) the “irreversible” neurological condition described in the current mefloquine product information to be permanent adverse reactions.","false","Biography information for The Countess of Mar",,"The Countess of Mar","HL4314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809610","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-27","<p>On 9 July 2017, the Secretary of State announced a package of measures to tackle abuse in this area. One of these was the Call for Evidence which closed on 10 November. We are considering the way forward and will announce the next steps in due course, with a view to implementing any changes as soon as practicable.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-27T15:30:09.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809610/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809610/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809610/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-19","Package Holidays: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the Government's timescale is for implementing any changes resulting from his Department's recent call for evidence on fraudulent gastric illness claims.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","120252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809611","Department of Health","false","2017-12-21","<p>No assessment has been made of the findings of this research. The Department funds research through the National Institute for Health Research which takes independent expert advice on which research proposals to support.</p>",,"Lord O'Shaughnessy",,"2017-12-21T15:38:01.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809611/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Shaughnessy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809611/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809611/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-12-19","Autism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether they have made an assessment of the findings of Matthew Mold et al on aluminium in brain tissue in autism, reported in the Journal of Trace Elements in Medicine and Biology; and if so, whether they will encourage further investigation of the link between the incidence of autism spectrum disorder and aluminium.","false","Biography information for The Countess of Mar",,"The Countess of Mar","HL4315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809612","Home Office","false","2018-01-05","<p>People can be mandated to attend deradicalisation programmes if it is necessary and proportionate to do so through the use of licence conditions if they are terrorist offenders on probation licence; or through being subject to Terrorism Prevention and Investigation Measures (TPIMs); or through being subject to a Temporary Exclusion Order (TEO).</p><p>Breaching probation licence conditions could lead to recall to prison; and breaching a TPIM or TEO condition could, on conviction, lead to a maximum sentence of five years in prison.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2018-01-05T14:40:36.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809612/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809612/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809612/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-12-19","Radicalism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what legal powers they have to mandate persons to attend deradicalisation programmes; and what sanctions and penalties exist for those who refuse to do so.","false","Biography information for Lord Marlesford",,"Lord Marlesford","HL4316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809613","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-12-29","<p>The Financial Guidance and Claims Bill was introduced in Parliament on 22 June 2017. This Bill enables the transfer of the regulation of claims management companies from the Ministry of Justice to the Financial Conduct Authority.</p><p> </p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-12-29T14:19:43.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809613/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809613/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/809613/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-12-19","Claims Management Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will set out a timescale for bringing forward legislative proposals on the regulation of claims management companies","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","120253"
